  "final_text": "Decoded. Verdict: **the target has not hardfaulted** \u2014 it's alive in thread mode, spinning in a polling loop.\n\n## Fault-register evidence (sticky SCB state, attached without reset)\n\n| Register | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| CFSR | `0x0` | No usage / bus / memmanage fault recorded |\n| HFSR | `0x0` | No forced or vector-table hardfault |\n| SHCSR | `0x0` | No fault handler active or pending |\n| ICSR.VECTACTIVE | `0` | **Thread mode** \u2014 not in any exception handler |\n| xPSR | `0x61000000` | IPSR = 0, confirms thread mode |\n| MMFAR / BFAR | `0xE000EDF8` | Reset/junk values, not valid (CFSR valid-bits clear) |\n\nThese bits are sticky \u2014 had a hardfault occurred since the last reset, CFSR/HFSR would still show it. They're all zero.\n\n## What it's actually doing\n\nHalted at `PC = 0x08002b76` (BLINKY.elf, F-PROJ-NUCLEO-L476RG), `SP = 0x20017FA8` (MSP, healthy). The disassembly around PC is a classic HAL flag-wait:\n\n```\n=> ldr r3, [r7, #12]     ; instance handle\n   ldr r3, [r3, #0]      ; ->Instance\n   ldr r2, [r3, #28]     ; read status register (offset 0x1C)\n   ldr r3, [r7, #8]      ; expected flag mask\n   ands r3, r2\n   cmp  r2, r3           ; loop until flag matches\n```\n\nThat's a busy-wait on a peripheral status flag (the shape matches a HAL `WaitOnFlag`-style helper), called from `LR = 0x08001EE3`. The symptom of \"hung/hardfaulted\" is really the firmware stuck waiting for a flag that never sets.\n\nTwo caveats:\n- The callstack frames came back unsymbolicated (`??` at 0x08002b76 / 0x08001be2) \u2014 if the flashed binary doesn't match this Debug ELF, the symbols (and any source-level conclusion) are unreliable. Worth confirming the board is running this exact build.\n- If you want to know *which* flag it's stuck on, I can read the governing peripheral (e.g. `stm32 debug read-peripheral` for the suspect \u2014 register offset 0x1C suggests something like an SR/ISR poll) and check the bit it's waiting for. Want me to chase that?"
